   The report said the drugs included 811.5 kilograms of cocaine, 46.7  
kilograms of heroin and 5,324 kilograms of marijuana. 
   Among the drug-trafficking-related suspects, 449 were foreigners and 2,  926 
were Portuguese drug addicts, the report said. 
   Earlier police reports show that drug users in Portugal have exceeded  
100,000 at present, making Portugal one of the leading countries in the  
European Union with the largest number of drug users. 
   The number is still on the rise with a growing population of young drug  
addicts, police officials said. 
